nother approach that works with the available ports. I'm realizing the core issue: port 10001 is where Ray's client API listens, but the Kubernetes service only exposes port 6379. The `ray://` protocol needs port 10001, which isn't accessible from outside the cluster. I need to either expose that port in the service definition or find another way to connect the driver to the cluster. Maybe the simplest approach is to just update the address string directly to `ray://ray-head:6379` and see if that works, even though it seems unconventional for the Ray Client protocol.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3687,"cache_read_input_tokens":30785,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3687},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08531ba3-9191-4f8b-8fcc-630c922ad1f1","uuid":"f25ea589-fffa-433e-b3fd-e6e856334ea7","request_id":"req_011CcQGfsrm6iMxUXpRmw6T3"}
